        <section class="timeline-section">
            <!-- Event 1 -->
            <div class="timeline-event">
                <div class="event-date">646 CE</div>
                <div class="event-content political">
                    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5c/Taika_Reforms.jpg/800px-Taika_Reforms.jpg" alt="Taika Reforms manuscript" class="event-image">
                    <div class="event-header">
                        <span class="event-icon">üéå</span>
                        <h3 class="event-title">Taika Reforms: Birth of Centralized Imperial Rule</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p class="event-description">The Taika Reforms fundamentally restructured Japanese government by abolishing private land ownership and establishing a centralized, Chinese-style imperial state with provinces ruled by imperial appointees.</p>
                    <div class="significance">
                        <h4>Historical Significance</h4>
                        <p>This represents Japan's first systematic transformation from clan-based chiefdoms into a unified, bureaucratic empire, laying the foundation for over a millennium of imperial authority.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="media-container">
                        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q_-5DGm9Ueg" target="_blank" class="video-link">
                            üé¨ Taika Reforms Documentary
                            <span class="url-display">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q_-5DGm9Ueg</span>
                        </a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Event 2 -->
            <div class="timeline-event">
                <div class="event-date">794 CE</div>
                <div class="event-content cultural">
                    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/Heian_Kyo.jpg/800px-Heian_Kyo.jpg" alt="Heian-ky≈ç capital reconstruction" class="event-image">
                    <div class="event-header">
                        <span class="event-icon">üèÆ</span>
                        <h3 class="event-title">Establishment of Heian-ky≈ç: Cultural Golden Age</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p class="event-description">Emperor Kammu moved the capital to Heian-ky≈ç (modern Kyoto), marking the beginning of Japan's classical era. This period witnessed the flourishing of distinctly Japanese arts and literature.</p>
                    <div class="significance">
                        <h4>Historical Significance</h4>
                        <p>The Heian Period represents Japan's cultural independence from Chinese models, developing native writing systems (hiragana/katakana) and aesthetic traditions.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Event 3 -->
            <div class="timeline-event">
                <div class="event-date">1192 CE</div>
                <div class="event-content military">
                    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3e/Minamoto_no_Yoritomo.jpg/800px-Minamoto_no_Yoritomo.jpg" alt="Minamoto no Yoritomo portrait" class="event-image">
                    <div class="event-header">
                        <span class="event-icon">‚öîÔ∏è</span>
                        <h3 class="event-title">Minamoto Yoritomo Becomes Sh≈çgun: Feudal Military Rule</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p class="event-description">Following the Genpei War, Minamoto Yoritomo received the title of Sei-i Taish≈çgun, establishing the Kamakura Shogunate and creating a dual-government system.</p>
                    <div class="significance">
                        <h4>Historical Significance</h4>
                        <p>This revolutionized Japanese political structure by transferring real power from the imperial court to the military aristocracy, establishing hereditary military rule.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Event 4 -->
            <div class="timeline-event">
                <div class="event-date">1543 CE</div>
                <div class="event-content economic">
                    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2e/Tanegashima_Matchlock.jpg/800px-Tanegashima_Matchlock.jpg" alt="Japanese matchlock firearm" class="event-image">
                    <div class="event-header">
                        <span class="event-icon">üö¢</span>
                        <h3 class="event-title">Portuguese Arrival & Introduction of Firearms</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p class="event-description">Portuguese traders landed on Tanegashima Island, introducing matchlock firearms and beginning the "Nanban trade" period, initiating Japan's first sustained contact with the West.</p>
                    <div class="significance">
                        <h4>Historical Significance</h4>
                        <p>Firearms democratized warfare, enabling warlords to challenge established powers and accelerating the unification process.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Event 5 -->
            <div class="timeline-event">
                <div class="event-date">1603 CE</div>
                <div class="event-content institutional">
                    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Tokugawa_Ieyasu2.JPG/800px-Tokugawa_Ieyasu2.JPG" alt="Tokugawa Ieyasu portrait" class="event-image">
                    <div class="event-header">
                        <span class="event-icon">üèØ</span>
                        <h3 class="event-title">Tokugawa Ieyasu Establishes Edo Shogunate</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p class="event-description">After victory at Sekigahara, Tokugawa Ieyasu established his shogunate in Edo. The regime created the "bakuhan" system, dividing Japan into 250+ domains under strict shogunal control.</p>
                    <div class="significance">
                        <h4>Historical Significance</h4>
                        <p>This brought 250 years of unprecedented peace and stability, creating a massive economic engine in Edo that laid the foundation for urban commercial culture.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="media-container">
                        <a href="https://study.com/academy/lesson/video/unification-of-japan-the-tokugawa-rule-1551-1868.html" target="_blank" class="video-link">
                            üé¨ Tokugawa Rule Documentary
                            <span class="url-display">https://study.com/academy/lesson/video/unification-of-japan-the-tokugawa-rule-1551-1868.html</span>
                        </a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Event 6 -->
            <div class="timeline-event">
                <div class="event-date">1635 CE</div>
                <div class="event-content political">
                    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/Dejima_Nagasaki_Japan.jpg/800px-Dejima_Nagasaki_Japan.jpg" alt="Dejima trading post illustration" class="event-image">
                    <div class="event-header">
                        <span class="event-icon">üö´</span>
                        <h3 class="event-title">Sakoku ("Closed Country") Policy Formalized</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p class="event-description">The Tokugawa shogunate issued the "Sakoku Edicts," prohibiting Japanese from leaving and severely restricting foreign contact. Only Dutch and Chinese traders were permitted at Nagasaki's Dejima Island.</p>
                    <div class="significance">
                        <h4>Historical Significance</h4>
                        <p>Isolation created cultural introversion but caused Japan to miss the Industrial Revolution, creating technological stagnation that would lead to vulnerability when Western powers forced opening.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Event 7 -->
            <div class="timeline-event">
                <div class="event-date">1853 CE</div>
                <div class="event-content economic">
                    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4b/Perry_Edo_Bay.jpg/800px-Perry_Edo_Bay.jpg" alt="Perry's Black Ships in Edo Bay" class="event-image">
                    <div class="event-header">
                        <span class="event-icon">üá∫üá∏</span>
                        <h3 class="event-title">Commodore Perry's "Black Ships" Arrival</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p class="event-description">U.S. Commodore Matthew Perry steamed into Edo Bay with four warships, delivering President Fillmore's demand that Japan open to trade. Perry's modern steam-powered ships demonstrated overwhelming technological superiority.</p>
                    <div class="significance">
                        <h4>Historical Significance</h4>
                        <p>This external shock exposed the fatal weaknesses of the Tokugawa system, triggering a political crisis that led to the shogunate's collapse and forcing Japan to confront its technological backwardness.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Event 8 -->
            <div class="timeline-event">
                <div class="event-date">1868 CE</div>
                <div class="event-content political">
                    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0f/Meiji_Emperor.jpg/800px-Meiji_Emperor.jpg" alt="Emperor Meiji portrait" class="event-image">
                    <div class="event-header">
                        <span class="event-icon">üåÖ</span>
                        <h3 class="event-title">Meiji Restoration: Modernization Revolution</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p class="event-description">Dissident samurai overthrew the Tokugawa shogunate, restoring Emperor Meiji to power. The government abolished feudalism, established a modern constitution, created a conscript army, and launched state-led industrialization.</p>
                    <div class="significance">
                        <h4>Historical Significance</h4>
                        <p>This represents one of history's most successful modernization programs, transforming a feudal society into Asia's first industrial power within 40 years.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="media-container">
                        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gkzxzM1HqpA" target="_blank" class="video-link">
                            üé¨ Meiji Restoration Documentary
                            <span class="url-display">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gkzxzM1HqpA</span>
                        </a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Event 9 -->
            <div class="timeline-event">
                <div class="event-date">1945 CE</div>
                <div class="event-content military">
                    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b2/Hiroshima_aftermath.jpg/800px-Hiroshima_aftermath.jpg" alt="Hiroshima aftermath" class="event-image">
                    <div class="event-header">
                        <span class="event-icon">üí£</span>
                        <h3 class="event-title">WWII Defeat & Post-War Reconstruction</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p class="event-description">Following atomic bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki, Japan surrendered unconditionally on August 15, 1945. The U.S. occupation implemented democratic reforms, dismantled the military, and created a new pacifist constitution.</p>
                    <div class="significance">
                        <h4>Historical Significance</h4>
                        <p>Defeat shattered Japan's imperial ambitions but created space for radical political and economic restructuring, leading to the "Japanese Miracle" economic recovery.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="media-container">
                        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WJLE2pnN9WY" target="_blank" class="video-link">
