                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Event 10 -->
            <div class="timeline-event">
                <div class="event-date">1964 CE</div>
                <div class="event-content cultural">
                    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Tokyo_Olympics_1964_opening_ceremony.jpg/800px-Tokyo_Olympics_1964_opening_ceremony.jpg" alt="1964 Tokyo Olympics opening ceremony" class="event-image">
                    <div class="event-header">
                        <span class="event-icon">üèÉ</span>
                        <h3 class="event-title">Tokyo Olympics: Japan's Global Rebirth</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p class="event-description">Tokyo became the first Asian city to host the Olympics, showcasing Japan's post-war recovery and technological sophistication. The games introduced the Shinkansen "bullet train" and satellite broadcasting.</p>
                    <div class="significance">
                        <h4>Historical Significance</h4>
                        <p>The 1964 Olympics served as Japan's "coming out" party, symbolizing its transformation from defeated enemy to peaceful, modern nation.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="media-container">
                        <a href="https://www.olympics.com/en/original-series/episode/tokyo-1964-official-film/" target="_blank" class="video-link">
